(166, 'home page', 57, 67, '<p align="center"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #993366; font-family: Georgia"><em>Chemistry<span>&nbsp; </span>Department</em></span></strong></p><span><p>&nbsp;</p><p><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black"><font face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;&nbsp; Chemistry<span>&nbsp; </span>department was established in the academic year<span>&nbsp; </span>1976/1977<span>&nbsp; </span>as Chemistry and Biology department , in 1978/1979<span>&nbsp; </span>separated to Chemistry<span>&nbsp; </span>department and Biology department.</font></span></p><p><span style="font-size: 11pt; color: black"><font face="Times New Roman">Now it has seven labs, as Organic, Inorganic, Analytical, Physical , Industrial, Biochemistry and Instrument labs.<br /><br />Graduate programs at M.Sc. and Ph.D. level in Chemistry started in academic year 1986/1987, and 2004/2005 respectively. The students are expected to successfully complete<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>150<span>&nbsp; </span>credit hours to graduate. Variety of research in various area of interest is undertaken by the staff members in this Department.</font></span></p></span>', 'ltr', 'left'),
